{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"6921","heading":"Office of Tribal Relations","label":"6921 Office of Tribal Relations","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/ch98/schI","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextSection 14 of the Federal Advisory Committee Act, referred to in subsec. (b)(7), is , which was set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees, and was repealed and restated as by , §§ 3(a), 7, , , 4361.section 14 of Pub. L. 92–463section 1013 of Title 5Pub. L. 117–286136 Stat. 4204Dec. 27, 2022","CodificationSection was enacted as part of the Federal Crop Insurance Reform and Department of Agriculture Reorganization Act of 1994, and not as part of the Department of Agriculture Reorganization Act of 1994 which in part comprises this chapter.","Amendments2018— designated existing provisions as subsec. (a), inserted heading, and added subsec. (b).Pub. L. 115–334"],"amendments":["References in TextSection 14 of the Federal Advisory Committee Act, referred to in subsec. (b)(7), is , which was set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees, and was repealed and restated as by , §§ 3(a), 7, , , 4361.section 14 of Pub. L. 92–463section 1013 of Title 5Pub. L. 117–286136 Stat. 4204Dec. 27, 2022","Amendments2018— designated existing provisions as subsec. (a), inserted heading, and added subsec. (b).Pub. L. 115–334"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall maintain in the Office of the Secretary an Office of Tribal Relations, which shall advise the Secretary on policies related to Indian tribes and carry out such other functions as the Secretary considers appropriate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Tribal Advisory Committee","label":"b Tribal Advisory Committee","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Definitions","label":"1 Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"Indian tribe","label":"A Indian tribe","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Indian tribe” has the meaning given the term in .section 5304 of title 25","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Relevant committees of Congress","label":"B Relevant committees of Congress","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Agriculture of the House of Representatives;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Agriculture, Nutrition, and Forestry of the Senate; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F1%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Indian Affairs of the Senate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":"Tribal organization","label":"C Tribal organization","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “tribal organization” has the meaning given the term in .section 5304 of title 25","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Establishment of committee","label":"2 Establishment of committee","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall establish an advisory committee, to be known as the Tribal Advisory Committee (referred to in this subsection as the “Committee”) to provide advice and guidance to the Secretary on matters relating to Tribal and Indian affairs.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Facilitation","label":"B Facilitation","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Committee shall facilitate, but not supplant, government-to-government consultation between the Department of Agriculture (referred to in this subsection as the “Department”) and Indian tribes.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Membership","label":"3 Membership","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"Composition","label":"A Composition","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"3 shall be appointed by the Secretary;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"1 shall be appointed by the chairperson of the Committee on Indian Affairs of the Senate;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FA%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"1 shall be appointed by the ranking member of the Committee on Indian Affairs of the Senate;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FA%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"1 shall be appointed by the chairperson of the Committee on Agriculture, Nutrition, and Forestry of the Senate;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"v","heading":null,"label":"v","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A/v","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FA%2Fv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"1 shall be appointed by the ranking member of the Committee on Agriculture, Nutrition, and Forestry of the Senate;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"vi","heading":null,"label":"vi","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A/vi","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FA%2Fvi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"2 shall be appointed by the chairperson of the Committee on Agriculture of the House of Representatives; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"vii","heading":null,"label":"vii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A/vii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FA%2Fvii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"2 shall be appointed by the ranking member of the Committee on Agriculture of the House of Representatives.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Nominations","label":"B Nominations","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"An Indian tribe.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A tribal organization.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A national or regional organization with expertise in issues relating to the duties of the Committee described in paragraph (4).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":"Diversity","label":"C Diversity","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To the maximum extent feasible, the Secretary shall ensure that the members of the Committee represent a diverse set of expertise on issues relating to geographic regions, Indian tribes, and the agricultural industry.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":"Limitation","label":"D Limitation","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"No member of the Committee shall be an officer or employee of the Federal Government.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":"Period of appointment; vacancies","label":"E Period of appointment; vacancies","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":"In general","label":"i In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/E/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FE%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/E/i/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/E/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FE%2Fi%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"subject to clause (ii), shall be appointed to a 3-year term; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/E/i/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/E/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FE%2Fi%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"may be reappointed to not more than 3 consecutive terms.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":"Initial staggering","label":"ii Initial staggering","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/E/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FE%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The first 3 appointments by the Secretary under paragraph (3)(A)(i) shall be for a 2-year term.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":"Vacancies","label":"iii Vacancies","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/E/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FE%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any vacancy in the Committee shall be filled in the same manner as the original appointment not more than 90 days after the date on which the position becomes vacant.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"F","heading":"Meetings","label":"F Meetings","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/F","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FF","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":"In general","label":"i In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/F/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/F","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FF%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Committee shall meet in person not less than twice each year.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":"Office of Tribal Relations representative","label":"ii Office of Tribal Relations representative","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/F/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/F","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FF%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not fewer than 1 representative from the Office of Tribal Relations of the Department shall be present at each meeting of the Committee.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":"Department of Interior representative","label":"iii Department of Interior representative","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/F/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/F","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FF%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Assistant Secretary for Indian Affairs of the Department of the Interior (or a designee) shall be present at each meeting of the Committee.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":"Nonvoting representatives","label":"iv Nonvoting representatives","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/F/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/3/F","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F3%2FF%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The individuals described in clauses (ii) and (iii) shall be nonvoting representatives at meetings of the Committee.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Duties of Committee","label":"4 Duties of Committee","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"identify evolving issues of relevance to Indian tribes relating to programs of the Department;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"communicate to the Secretary the issues identified under subparagraph (A);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F4%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/C/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F4%2FC%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the issues identified under subparagraph (A);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/C/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F4%2FC%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"issues raised at the Tribal, regional, or national level; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/C/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F4%2FC%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"issues relating to any Tribal consultation carried out by the Department;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F4%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"discuss issues and proposals for changes to the regulations, policies, and procedures of the Department that impact Indian tribes;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F4%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"identify priorities and provide advice on appropriate strategies for Tribal consultation on issues at the Tribal, regional, or national level regarding the Department;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"F","heading":null,"label":"F","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/F","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F4%2FF","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"ensure that pertinent issues of the Department are brought to the attention of an Indian tribe in a timely manner so that timely feedback from an Indian tribe can be obtained; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"G","heading":null,"label":"G","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4/G","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F4%2FG","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"identify and propose solutions to any interdepartmental barrier between the Department and other Federal agencies.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":"Reports","label":"5 Reports","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F5%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F5%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the activities of the Committee during the previous year; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F5%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"recommendations for legislative or administrative action for the following year.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Response from Secretary","label":"B Response from Secretary","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F5%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F5%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/5/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F5%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the relevant committees of Congress.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":"Compensation of members","label":"6 Compensation of members","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Members of the Committee shall be compensated at a rate equal to the daily equivalent of the annual rate of basic pay prescribed for level IV of the Executive Schedule under for each day (including travel time) during which the member is engaged in the performance of the duties of the Committee.section 5315 of title 5","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":"Federal Advisory Committee Act exemption","label":"7 Federal Advisory Committee Act exemption","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s6921/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs6921%2Fb%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Section 14 of the Federal Advisory Committee Act (5 U.S.C. App.) shall not apply to the Committee.1See References in Text note below.1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
